The power OF FEET! 🦶 

Is training barefoot one of those things that will change your life forever? Not entirely.

Is training barefoot one of those things that can change your training entirely? Absolutely. Here’s why.

Squatting in running shoes is like trying to push a truck with your hands, but putting styrofoam in between you and the truck. Sure the truck will move but it will seem like you’re losing power. To where as spreading your fingers, firmly grasping the truck and pushing will feel wayyyy better.

If you’re squatting and experiencing knee pain, there could be a chance you’re putting to much pressure on the front of your foot / toes instead of 100% of the whole foot (33% big toe 33% pinky 33% heel). A simply barefoot squat while loading the whole foot, can help teach to use the whole foot. 

There’s no “one way fix all” method to anything. But there are things like this that can help most athletes get stronger and healthier!

WHAT MOBILITY MOVEMENTS TO DO BEFORE YOUR WORKOUT.

This is the fun part while looking to get a healthy body in or even outside the gym.

Things to look for when creating your mobility workout 🔽

▶️ What areas need improvement (lacks range of motion) 

▶️ Any pain from old injuries, previous workout soreness? 

▶️Core strengthening exercises seeing as how most compounds require core stability & strength.

▶️ Balance / stability movement (I like to add unilateral work with this as well just to be over all improving but saving time 

▶️Movement specific loaded movement (here I like to add movements that are not on the specific block as much like kettle bell swings)

And begin the workout! This usually takes me 12-15 min to do. 

The main workout is 30-40min and today I had 3 compounds with 4+ sets each. 

So many ways to go about training and there is no one fit all. But! Programming around this style of training has brought myself and my athletes better range of motion, more energy throughout the day and better results in the gym!

Spent all day trying to edit this video to be under 2 minutes, just to find out insta only allows 90 seconds 🤣

I added the full video to the YouTube and the link is in the bio 🫡 it’s a little over 2 minutes for those who need a lil guidance.

Its a breakfast smoothie, 2 meals and veggies for snacks you can eat though out the day! Disregard any errors as I did everything as I went on. 

Took a little over an hour to prepare the food. 

I forgot a food scale so here’s some math to calculate serving size. 

If ground Turkey comes in a 16oz container…
After cooking it, you can evenly divide the whole container into 2/3/4 meals.
The container says (4 servings) per containers 
Take the MACRO you want to calculate and multiply it by 4. (Let’s use protein as an example) 
4 servings X 21 protein is 84 grams of protein total. 84 divided by 3 meals (like I did in the video) is 28 PROTEIN per meal. 

Or just weigh your food 😂 food scales are at Walmart & target and a great investment.

BREAKFAST SMOOTHIE 
12 Oz almond milk 2 pro 2 carb 5 fat
2 scoops of Whey 48 pro 6 carb 2 fat
Banana 0 pro 27 carb 0 fat
Apple 0 pro 25 carb 0 fat
Strawberries 0 pro 7 carb 0 fat

^50 protein 67 Carb 7 fat^

GROUND TURKEY MEAL
5oz Ground turkey 28 pro 0 carb 10 fat 
2 servings of sweet potatoes 4 pro 50 carb 0 fat 
Peppers 0 pro 2 carb 0 fat 
Onions 0 pro 2 carb 0 fat 
Mushrooms 0 pro 1 carb 0 fat 
Spinach 0 pro 1 carb 0 fat 
Avocado oil 11 fat 

^32 Protein 56 Carb 21 Fat^

GROUND BEEF MEAL
5oz Ground beef 80/20 26 pro 0 carb 30 fat
2 servings of sweet potatoes 4 pro 50 carb 0 fat 
Peppers 0 pro 2 carb 0 fat 
Onions 0 pro 2 carb 0 fat 
Mushrooms 0 pro 1 carb 0 fat 
Spinach 0 pro 1 carb 0 fat 
Avocado oil 11 fat 

^30 Protein 56 Carb 41 Fat^

PRE WORKOUT 
Blueberries 
Black berries 

POST WORKOUT SHAKE
Whey protein 24 pro 3 carb 1 fat

SNACK ON THE VEGGIES 😁

^136 Protein 180 carb 70 Fat^
I didn’t add the extra veggies and carbs but it is important to do so! Establish a baseline and stay consistent.

If you wanted to add more protein, I’d just eat 1-2 more lean Turkey meals throughout the day and adjust accordingly.

Thanks for reading!

⬇️ READ BELOW IF YOU’RE STRUGGLING WITH WEIGHT GAIN 

First things first. Are you eating enough? 

Skipping breakfast, protein bars / coffee for breakfast then eating a salad and big dinner is not enough. A 180lb male or even a 140lb female, eating 1600- 2000 calories a day while hitting the gym for hours, will not help you gain weight. (Goal depending)

Secondly, are you doing too much? 6 days a week in the gym, 4 movements 4 sets of 10-12 reps, super sets. drop sets and OVER TRAINING (athlete depending) is really putting you in a bigger caloric deficit if you’ve haven’t gotten to the point where your body has ADAPTED to the volume you’re putting it through. 

Be okay with training 3-4 days a week 3 movements, 3 sets, longer breaks and moving less! (But stay healthy. Mobility is lotion apply is daily especially when gaining weight).

I hope this helps! Let’s get to work!

23lb weight gain in 3 months! 

📍142lb-165lb

SQUAT 185 - 225 PR
BENCH 115 - 175 PR
Deadlift 185 - 315 PR

Let’s be real. Being 18 years old, doing just about anything will make you grow. Nate was not eating as much as he should, sleep schedule off, workouts were the type of workouts with “the bros”. 

The simple changes we made were eating breakfast every morning (I feel like this is a very important first step to those struggling with weight gain)

Waking up earlier in order to get ready to eat. The diet isn’t super crazy but starting each day with 2-3 different types of fruits, protein source like eggs or protein shake with egg whites and a complex carb like oats. From there eating anything he could 3 more times a day. Yes, anything.

He eats good and out about 3 times a week.

The weight training program is very basic and works on main compound movements, unilateral movements, Calisthenics and mobility. Rarely I let him attempt a 1RM but often he’s able to hit a 12/10/8/6 or 5. 

Just show up and put out. You’ll notice the change you want to see. Next 3 months we will be looking to gain weight but will up his calories to see the results and go from there. His main goal is to be stronger than me and look like Baki so he’s on the right track. 🤩
